Key Match Events: Khama Billiat converted a penalty in the first half to give Zimbabwe a 1-0 lead
Namibia had a chance hit the upright in front of goal
Daniel Msendami's shot also hit the upright for Zimbabwe
Douglas Mapfumo could have scored but chose to shoot instead of passing
Post-Match Reflections: Zimbabwe now tops Group J with five points
They are one point ahead of Kenya and Cameroon who are second and third respectively
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at an empty Orlando Stadium in Soweto, Johannesburg, South Africa
Zimbabwe's win is their first in AFCON and World Cup qualifiers since their FIFA ban was lifted
